it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.example

Class ObjectHierarchyTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.example.ObjectHierarchyTest

  • public class ObjectHierarchyTest
extends java.lang.Object
    A runnable example to see the object java/semantic mapping behaviour.

    This implementation shown how it is possible to instantiate java objects and map them with respect to the semantic defined in the package: it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.objects.

    In particular, this example generated an Object of each shape and writes/reads it to/from the ontology by performing some manipulation for showing purposes. Finally, the generated semantic structure will be saved in a file specified by: ONTO_FILE_SAVING_PATH.

    This example uses the basics semantic representation of the objects hierarchy described by the empty ontology (only T-box) available as a file at the ONTO_FILE_LOADING_PATH. Check out other interesting ontology in the folder: //scene_identification_tracking/files/semantic-scene-library.

    REMARK: in this example the reasoner of the ontology is never user.

    File: it.emarolab.scene_identification_tracking.semanticSceneLibrary.objects.Semantics
